# Monorepo & build conventions (AD-019, AD-020, AD-021)

> **M0 stub.** This rule activates once the monorepo is scaffolded. At **M0**, pin the tool versions
> (Node LTS, pnpm, Blockly, Vite, Vitest, Turborepo, Changesets) in `docs/ROADMAP.md` §"Version pins"
> and replace the `<pin>` placeholders below with the chosen versions (AD-021).

## Layout
- pnpm workspaces + Turborepo. Packages (AD-019/020): `@transon/editor-core` (pure TS) →
  `@transon/editor-blockly` (Zelos) → `editor-ui` (internal React) → `@transon/editor-element`
  (vanilla + `<transon-editor>`) + `@transon/editor-react`.
- **Dependency direction is one-way:** core → blockly → ui → element/react. Never import "up".

## Hard constraints
- **No engine runtime in any published bundle** (AD-008). The engine is host-provided via
  `EngineProvider`; engine adapters and Pyodide live only in `examples/`/tests, never in package deps.
- `@transon/editor-core` stays free of Blockly/React/DOM/engine deps (AD-016) so it builds and
  unit-tests headless.
- Build with **Vite library mode**; ship ESM + types per package. Test with **Vitest**.
- Version/release with **Changesets**; one changeset per user-visible change.

